  "text": "Type 1 diabetic patients show increased sensitivity to salt, more marked in patients with microalbuminuria [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] but the cause remains unclear. Our hypothesis was that reduced 11b-HSD2 activity may play a role in the pathogenesis of nephropathy in patients with type 1 diabetes or may contribute to the increased salt sensitivity that characterises diabetic nephropaths.",
